com.xuggle.xuggler
Class IProperty

java.lang.Object
  com.xuggle.ferry.RefCounted
      com.xuggle.xuggler.IProperty

public class IProperty
extends RefCounted

Represents settable properties that effect how Xuggler objects operate.

For example, setting the "b" property on an IStreamCoder sets the bit-rate the coder will attempt to encode at.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Compares two values, returning true if the underlying objects in native code are the same object. That means you can have two different Java objects, but when you do a comparison, you'll find out they are the EXACT same object.
